comment: Decompose a ` DVecH ` vector expressed as an ordered pair into the sum of two components, the first from the translation group vector base of ` DVecA ` and the other from the one-dimensional vector subspace ` E ` . Part of Lemma M of [Crawley] p. 121, line 18. We represent their e, sigma, f by ` <. ( _I |`` B ) , ( _I |`` T ) >. ` , ` U ` , ` <. F , O >. ` . We swapped the order of vector sum (their juxtaposition i.e. composition) to show ` <. F , O >. ` first. Note that ` O ` and ` ( _I |`` T ) ` are the zero and one of the division ring ` E ` , and ` ( _I |`` B ) ` is the zero of the translation group. ` S ` is the scalar product.
